<div data-type="exercise" id="fs-idm139949520"><div data-type="problem" id="fs-idm137614176">
<p id="fs-idm139601840">Consider the orbitals shown here in outline.</p>
<span data-type="media" id="fs-idm55642896" class="scaled-down" data-alt="This figure contains three diagrams. In x, a circle is drawn with a dot at the center. In y, two nearly ellipsoid shapes are oriented horizontally with a dot between them. In z, four shapes like those in y are oriented in an x shape with a dot at the center.">
<img src="/resources/5eed3a0d6a877a567c38b39f3191390053c62e38/CNX_Chem_06_03_OrbOutline_img.jpg" data-media-type="image/jpeg" alt="This figure contains three diagrams. In x, a circle is drawn with a dot at the center. In y, two nearly ellipsoid shapes are oriented horizontally with a dot between them. In z, four shapes like those in y are oriented in an x shape with a dot at the center."/>
</span>
<p id="fs-idm9922432">(a) What is the maximum number of electrons contained in an orbital of type (x)? Of type (y)? Of type (z)?</p>
<p id="fs-idm66251616">(b) How many orbitals of type (x) are found in a shell with <em data-effect="italics">n</em> = 2? How many of type (y)? How many of type (z)?</p>
<p id="fs-idm95832304">(c) Write a set of quantum numbers for an electron in an orbital of type (x) in a shell with <em data-effect="italics">n</em> = 4. Of an orbital of type (y) in a shell with <em data-effect="italics">n</em> = 2. Of an orbital of type (z) in a shell with <em data-effect="italics">n</em> = 3.</p>
<p id="fs-idm165503392">(d) What is the smallest possible <em data-effect="italics">n</em> value for an orbital of type (x)? Of type (y)? Of type (z)?</p>
<p id="fs-idm63155984">(e) What are the possible <em data-effect="italics">l</em> and <em data-effect="italics">m<sub>l</sub></em> values for an orbital of type (x)? Of type (y)? Of type (z)?</p></div>
<div data-type="solution" id="fs-idm82172944">
<p id="fs-idm90450992">(a) x. 2, y. 2, z. 2; (b) x. 1, y. 3, z. 0; (c) x. 4 0 0 <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline"><semantics><mrow><mrow><mspace width="0.2em"/><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>,</mo></mrow></mrow><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content"><mrow><mspace width="0.2em"/><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>,</mo></mrow></annotation-xml></semantics></math> y. 2 1 0 <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline"><semantics><mrow><mrow><mspace width="0.2em"/><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>,</mo></mrow></mrow><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content"><mrow><mspace width="0.2em"/><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>,</mo></mrow></annotation-xml></semantics></math> z. 3 2 0 <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline"><semantics><mrow><mrow><mspace width="0.2em"/><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>;</mo></mrow></mrow><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content"><mrow><mspace width="0.2em"/><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>;</mo></mrow></annotation-xml></semantics></math> (d) x. 1, y. 2, z. 3; (e) x. <em data-effect="italics">l</em> = 0, <em data-effect="italics">m<sub>l</sub></em> = 0, y. <em data-effect="italics">l</em> = 1, <em data-effect="italics">m<sub>l</sub> =</em> &#8211;1, 0, or <em data-effect="italics">+</em>1, z. <em data-effect="italics">l</em> = 2, <em data-effect="italics">m<sub>l</sub></em> = &#8211;2, &#8211;1, 0, +1, +2</p></div></div>
